console.log("Welcome");

//REPL
Node

// create directory
mkdir nodeProject

// create file
type nul  > index.js

// go to the editor mode
node
.editor
ctl + D to return

// Exit from editor
.exit;

//Node.js core Module
A set of function you want to include in your application. it is a set of built in  module

//create packages.json
npm init

// Install chalk for coloring output
npm i chalk@4.1.2

// Install validator
npm i validator

// Install nodemon
npm i nodemon -g
nodemon -v

Note : 
Problem :: when you got the issue like as
nodemon : File C:\Users\HP\AppData\Roaming\npm\nodemon.ps1 cannot be loaded because running scripts is disabled on this system. For more information, 
see about_Execution_Policies at https:/go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=135170.
At line:1 char:1

Solution : 
1. Open Windows PowerShell with Run as Administrator
2. Run this command: Set-ExecutionPolicy Unrestricted

and run nodemon <filename.js> for first time then it will run automatically on any changes into file.
for exit type ctrl + c
